## Web Crawler Workflow

Here is the complete flow, step by step:

| Step | Component | What Happens |
|---|---|---|
| **1** | Seed URLs → URL Frontier | Initial URLs are loaded into the frontier |
| **2** | URL Frontier → HTML Fetcher | Frontier selects the next URL to crawl (based on priority + politeness) |
| **3a** | HTML Fetcher | Fetches the URL from the frontier queue |
| **3b** | DNS Resolver | Resolves domain to IP address |
| **3c** | Internet | Downloads the page content |
| **4** | HTML Parser | Parses raw HTML into clean, structured content |
| **5** | Duplicate Detection | Hashes the content; checks if it's been seen before |
| **6** | Modular Services (via Kafka) | Passes content to Analytics, Image Download, URL Extractor |
| **7** | URL Filter | Filters out unwanted discovered URLs (robots.txt, blacklists, etc.) |
| **8** | URL Seen Detector | Checks if filtered URLs have been crawled before; new ones go back to frontier |

