## Interview Tips & Summary

### Key Questions an Interviewer Might Ask

**Q: How do you handle politeness?**
> The URL Frontier has per-domain queues with configurable crawl delays. We respect `robots.txt` and enforce minimum intervals between requests to the same host.

**Q: How do you detect duplicate content?**
> We use SHA-256 hashing for exact duplicates and SimHash for near-duplicate detection. The hashes are stored in a fast key-value store like Redis.

**Q: How do you scale to 1 billion pages/month?**
> At ~385 pages/second, we need ~400+ parallel fetcher threads. The architecture is horizontally scalable — we add fetcher workers and parser workers independently. The URL Frontier is a distributed queue (Kafka/Redis), and storage is distributed (Cassandra for metadata, S3 for raw HTML).

**Q: What is the URL Seen Detector?**
> A Bloom Filter (in-memory) backed by persistent URL Storage. It tells us which URLs we've already crawled so we don't revisit them. Unseen URLs are added to the URL Frontier and stored persistently.

**Q: Why Kafka?**
> Kafka decouples the URL Extractor from the URL Frontier. If downstream services (analytics, image downloader) are slow, they don't block the main crawl pipeline. It also provides durability (messages are persisted) and allows replay if a service crashes.

**Q: How do you handle JavaScript-rendered pages?**
> For known JS-heavy domains, we use headless browsers (Puppeteer). For the majority of pages, a simple HTTP fetch is sufficient and much cheaper.

### Quick Component Summary

| Component | Role | Key Design Choice |
|---|---|---|
| Seed URLs | Starting points | Curated high-authority domains or feeds |
| URL Frontier | Queue + scheduler | BFS + priority + politeness queues |
| DNS Resolver | Domain → IP | Local DNS cache to reduce latency |
| HTML Fetcher | Downloads pages | Thread pool, optional headless browser |
| HTML Parser | Cleans + structures content | Extracts text + links |
| Duplicate Detection | Avoids redundant storage | SimHash for near-duplicates |
| Content Cache | Fast content lookup | Redis or Memcached |
| Content Storage | Persistent page store | S3 + Cassandra metadata |
| Kafka | Message bus | Decouples modular services |
| URL Extractor | Finds new links | Modular service consuming Kafka |
| URL Filter | Removes bad URLs | robots.txt, blacklists, extensions |
| URL Seen Detector | Tracks visited URLs | Bloom Filter + persistent store |
| URL Storage | Persists crawl history | Cassandra/DynamoDB |
